The paper analyzes revenue loss in a market with bidders and values, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and mechanism design (cs.EC). The analysis involves probability distributions, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents a solution to an open question, which could be of interest to the machine learning community (cs.LG).
